  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to support the engagement of upland communities in agroforestry and promotion of access to markets through value chains that incentivize watershed management. This will include: 1) linking community producers to the corporate value chains; 2) engaging private sector stakeholders in water security planning; and 3) establishing/improving innovative financing schemes to support upstream watershed, forest and WRM activities and environmentally sustainable livelihoods. The project is funded by USAID and LWR is a subcontractor under DAI.</narrative>
